We recommended that:

a. Management prepare the adjusting journal entries to recognize the effect of the change in the estimate of residual value for PPE items which were fully depreciated but were still serviceable to faithfully represent their respective CVs. 

b.  Adjust the CV of the individual PPE item and prepare an adjusting entry with a debit to Prior Period Adjustment of ₱4,146.67 and a credit to the respective Accumulated Depreciation of the affected PPE accounts;

c. Prepare the adjusting journal entries to correct the balance of the Buildings and Other Structures account;


d. Determine the economic useful life of the DRRM Operation Center and compute for its corresponding depreciation.

We recommended that Management consider the following:

Instruct the Municipal Planning and Development Office to require the Program of Work before development projects are included in the Annual Investment Plan (AIP) to ensure timely and efficient implementation;


Ensure that only feasible PPAs are included in the AIP.  Programs and projects with problems, issues, complaints, and some other reasons should not be considered;


Formulate/develop specific strategies/solutions to effectively implement development projects.  Consider formulating a timetable within which to start and complete the unimplemented projects; and


Hire additional personnel to fill-up vacant positions in the Municipal Engineering Office.

We recommended the following courses of action:

For the MHO to ensure the timely preparation of BS as provided in Philhealth Circular No. 2016-0013 to assure receipt of additional funds for the provision of quality health services;

 For the MAccO to recognize in the books of accounts all billed PFP claims as provided in the above guidelines as well as to consistently apply the accrual basis of accounting on all transactions.

We strongly recommended the following:
a. For the Mystical Kabayan Tourism Culture and Arts Council, Inc. (MKTCAC) to cease collection of Green and Cultural Fees and to immediately remit actual collections from CY 2013 up to present to the Local Treasury supported by the Council’s Annual Financial Report and other pertinent documents;
b. For the Municipal Treasurer to immediately account all remitted collections from Green and Cultural Fee and to deposit the same under a Trust account with an Authorized Government Depository Bank; 
c. For the Municipal Treasurer or his/her duly authorized representative to assume the collection of Green and Cultural Fees and issue the prescribed official receipts held by the Municipal Government; and
d. For the Municipal Accountant to maintain separate books for a Green Fund and a Cultural Fund to ensure that the objectives for which the Fees were created are attained.
